.SH "NAME"
Locale::Maketext::Lexicon::Tie \- Use tied hashes as lexicons for Maketext
.SH "VERSION"
.IX Header "VERSION"
version 1.00
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 5
\&    package Hello::I18N;
\&    use base \*(AqLocale::Maketext\*(Aq;
\&    use Locale::Maketext::Lexicon {
\&        en => [ Tie => [ DB_File => \*(Aqen.db\*(Aq ] ],
\&    };
.Ve
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This module lets you easily \f(CW\*(C`tie\*(C'\fR the \f(CW%Lexicon\fR hash to a database
or other data sources.  It takes an array reference of arguments, and
passes them directly to \f(CW\*(C`tie()\*(C'\fR.
.PP
Entries will then be fetched whenever it is used; this module does not
cache them.
